In 3 recent review of a similar collection of frag- ments, it was objected that the compilers of such books do not follow some accepted numeration, such as that of the Teubner series, In this book it was impossible. New discoveries had made both Bergk and Hiller-Crusius out of date, and the edition of Diehl, even if it was to contain all the fragments and notices gathered in these volumes, had not been completely published. I hope that the numeration- tables will do something to ease the difficulty of tracing old favourites to their new homes.
